    "Some researchers use the Zipf 's law (Ryland Williams et al., 2015) to set thresholds of top n words or phrases to report their word analysis.",
    "However, thresholds when used without consideration for the size or the information that words can provide about the dataset (Genzel and Charniak, 2002) can give readers and analysts an incomplete vision of the dataset.",
    "Therefore, we used percentiles, specifically divided the keyword eigenvector centrality into four or quartiles to provide readers and analysts a wider view of the keywords that were most (x > Q75th), average (Q75th<x > Q50th) and in the periphery of the networks (Q50th<x > Q25th and x < Q25th).",
    "Frontiers in Education 05 frontiersin.org",
    "We provide two levels of descriptive analysis by using network analysis, an overview of all literature reviews about gamification and a discriminated analysis year by year."
  ],
